.TH FYMD4C 1 "July 2026" "" "General Commands Manual"
.nh
.ad l
.
.SH NAME
.
fymd4c \- convert Markdown to ANSI, HTML, or heal mid-stream Markdown
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.
.B fymd4c
.RI [ OPTION ]...\&
.RI [ FILE ]
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.
.B fymd4c
is the single command line front-end over \fBlibfymd4c\fR. It renders
Markdown to ANSI (the default, for terminal display, with progressive and
self-healing streaming and syntax-highlighted fenced code), to HTML, or it
heals incomplete/mid-stream Markdown into well-formed Markdown.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.
.SS General options:
.
.TP
.BR -o ", " --output= \fIOUTFILE\fR
Write output to \fIOUTFILE\fR instead of \fBstdout\fR(3)
.
.TP
.BR -t ", " --format= \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: \fBansi\fR (default), \fBheal\fR, \fBhtml\fR
.
.TP
.BR -s ", " --stat
Measure time of input parsing
.
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Display help and exit
.
.TP
.BR -v ", " --version
Display version and exit
.
.TP
.B --heal
Heal incomplete markdown before rendering
.
.SS ANSI output options (\fB--format=ansi\fR):
.
.TP
.B --color= \fIMODE\fR
Color output: \fBauto\fR (default; enabled only when stdout is a terminal), \fBon\fR, or \fBoff\fR
.
.TP
.B --width= \fIWIDTH\fR
Layout width: \fBauto\fR (default; from \fB$COLUMNS\fR or the terminal, else 80), \fBinf\fR (unlimited, no wrapping), or a column count. Tables are laid out and all text is word-wrapped to this width.
.
.TP
.B --style= \fIFILE\fR
Load styling from the YAML file \fIFILE\fR instead of the embedded default.
.
.TP
.B --background= \fIMODE\fR
Assume terminal background: \fBauto\fR (default), \fBdark\fR, or \fBlight\fR.
.
.TP
.B --reverse
Render fenced code blocks in reverse "bubble" style.
.
.TP
.B --language= \fILANG\fR
Treat the input as raw source code and render it directly as one fenced block instead of parsing Markdown. \fBauto\fR detects the language from the input file name using the libfyts catalogue. With standard input, \fBauto\fR renders an unlabeled plain-code fence. This mode also works with \fB--stream-progressive\fR.
.
.TP
.B --table-size= \fIMODE\fR
Table sizing: fit to content or to width.
.
.TP
.B --stream
Render incrementally (push mode): output is emitted as input arrives, committed up to the last safe sync point. With healing off, the result is identical to a non-streamed ANSI render.
.
.TP
.B --stream-progressive
Live progressive render: input is read incrementally and the active region (the part after the last safe sync point) is updated in place. On a terminal, each update moves the cursor up and reprints only the changed lines; when output is not a terminal, the final reconstructed screen is written (identical to a non-streamed render).
.
.TP
.B --max-active-lines= \fIN\fR
Cap the progressive active region to \fIN\fR lines (0 => unlimited).
.
.TP
.B --max-lines= \fIN\fR
Cap ANSI output to \fIN\fR rendered terminal rows (0 => unlimited). Short output is not padded.
.
.TP
.B --line-overflow= \fIMODE\fR
Select the rendered-row overflow policy: \fBscroll\fR (retain the newest rows) or \fBhead-tail\fR (retain both ends with an omission row).
.
.TP
.B --line-head= \fIN\fR|\fBbalanced\fR
In head-tail mode, retain exactly \fIN\fR head rows or split the available content rows between the head and tail. The extra row in a balanced even-sized viewport goes to the tail.
.
.TP
.B --line-separator= \fIFORMAT\fR
Set the head-tail omission row. \fIFORMAT\fR must contain one \fB%d\fR for the omitted rendered-row count; \fB%%\fR emits a literal percent sign.
.
.SS HTML output options (\fB--format=html\fR):
.
.TP
.BR -f ", " --full-html
Generate full HTML document, including header
.
.TP
.BR -x ", " --xhtml
Generate XHTML instead of HTML
.
.TP
.B --fverbatim-entities
Do not translate entities
.
.TP
.B --html-title=TITLE
Sets the title of the document
.
.TP
.B --html-css=URL
In full HTML or XHTML mode add a css link
.
.SS Markdown dialect options:
.
.TP
.B --commonmark
CommonMark (the default)
.
.TP
.BR --gfm ", " --github
Github Flavored Markdown
.
.PP
Note: dialect options are equivalent to some combination of the extension and
suppression flags below.
.
.SS Markdown extension options:
.
.TP
.B --fadmonitions
Enable admonitions
.
.TP
.B --fcollapse-whitespace
Collapse non-trivial whitespace
.
.TP
.B --ffootnotes
Enable footnote references ([^label])
.
.TP
.B --fhard-soft-breaks
Force all soft breaks to act as hard breaks
.
.TP
.B --fhighlight
Enable highlight spans (==text==)
.
.TP
.B --flatex-math
Enable LaTeX style mathematics spans
.
.TP
.B --fpermissive-atx-headers
Allow ATX headers without delimiting space
.
.TP
.B --fpermissive-email-autolinks
Allow e-mail autolinks without "<", ">" and "mailto:"
.
.TP
.B --fpermissive-url-autolinks
Allow URL autolinks without "<" and ">" delimiters
.
.TP
.B --fpermissive-www-autolinks
Allow WWW autolinks without any scheme (e.g., "www.example.com")
.
.TP
.B --fpermissive-autolinks
Enable all 3 of the above permissive autolinks options
.
.TP
.B --fspoilers
Enable spoiler spans (||hidden text||)
.
.TP
.B --fstrikethrough
Enable strikethrough spans
.
.TP
.B --fsubscripts
Enable subscript spans (~text~)
.
.TP
.B --fsuperscripts
Enable superscript spans (^text^)
.
.TP
.B --ftables
Enable tables
.
.TP
.B --ftasklists
Enable task lists
.
.TP
.B --funderline
Enable underline spans
.
.TP
.B --fwiki-links
Enable wiki links
.
.SS Markdown suppression options:
.
.TP
.B --fno-html-blocks
Disable raw HTML blocks
.
.TP
.B --fno-html-spans
Disable raw HTML spans
.
.TP
.B --fno-html
Same as \fB--fno-html-blocks --fno-html-spans\fR
.
.TP
.B --fno-indented-code
Disable indented code blocks
.
.SH SEE ALSO
.
https://github.com/mity/md4c
.
